rComments: Si t'aimes pas l'histoire/politique/lire en général, prends pas ce cours... Toutes les dates des tests/travaux/examens sont postés en avance, les requis sur les travaux sont clairs, mais ces slides/lectures sont VRAIMENT LONGUEEES ET ONT BEAUCOUP D'ÉCRITURE Honestly, lisez TOUTES ses slides/textes... you'll need it Otherwise Mme Forest est vrm fine

rComments: Pire prof! J'ai détesté le cours en ligne... Project à remettre chaque semaine. Malgré tout l'effort mis, elle est très difficile à plaire,... j'espère passer le cours, mais à se point si, j'ai aucun espoir. (J'ai deux autres amies qui ont pris ce cours, et elles aussi ont la même opinion que moi) Je ne vais plus jamais prendre un cours en ligne.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Tough grader']

rComments: More reading than the norm but that's only because it's an online class. Exams are done at home with access to all your notes so there's no valid reason to do poorly if you've done all the previous work.  Material isn't the most interesting, as most basic 1st year classes are, but prof is very enthusiastic. Best part is staying in your pjs at home!

A lot of reading materiel since it's an online class. If you have questions she will explain it to you in the best way she can. Exams are take home and very hard. Exam questions are tricky and require a lot of studying. 5 % essays are easy and can boost up your grade. Very nice professor.
She is really sweet and gives a lot of help if you go and see her during her office hours.
